headline.main: 76 BILLIONS SPENT IN U.S. FISCAL YEAR; 71 of the Total Were for War -- Public Debt Up to 140 Billions, Deficit to 55

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 30 -- The United States ended its fiscal year tonight with a record of expenditures of more than $76,000,000,000, receipts of more than $21,000,000,000, a gross public debt of more that $140,000,000,000 and a deficit of more than $55,000,000,000.
